        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 7:16AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 716 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Downtown Concord, or near Mt Pleasant, moving east at
40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gold Hill, Rockwell, High Rock, Mt Pleasant, and High Rock Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon EDT for the
Piedmont of North Carolina.</instruction>
